    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 12-15 min, then remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/grilled-miso-chicken-thigh-with-edamame-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>miso</strong>, 1/3 of your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Stir it all together until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>miso marinade</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/grilled-miso-chicken-thigh-with-edamame-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced chicken</strong> to the <strong>miso marinade</strong> and mix it all together until fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/grilled-miso-chicken-thigh-with-edamame-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Put the tray under the grill for 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through and starting to char (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/grilled-miso-chicken-thigh-with-edamame-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, cut your<strong> cucumber </strong>in half lengthways (scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon and discard) then dice roughly</p><p>Add your<strong> edamame beans</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water </strong>all over them to refresh them, then run under <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> until cool</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> as finely as you can</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/grilled-miso-chicken-thigh-with-edamame-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining chopped ginger</strong> with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar</strong>,<strong> remaining sesame oil </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame ginger</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/grilled-miso-chicken-thigh-with-edamame-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> diced cucumber</strong>, <strong>refreshed edamame beans </strong>and<strong> sliced shallot</strong> to the bowl with the<strong> sesame ginger dressing</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>edamame salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/grilled-miso-chicken-thigh-with-edamame-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>edamame salad </strong>over the <strong>cooked rice </strong>and drizzle over any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sesame ginger</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>grilled miso chicken</strong> and sprinkle over your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
